<br>
I'm telling you right now, aside from the mentioning of a trigger mob, or the best was to approach a plane (kill order, priority) this discussion is nothing more than one rep saying, hey we need to treat plane of air as a total entity (like TovN), and we need to divide plane of fire into 2 segments. <br>
<br>
Then another rep will post and say, no, i think fire and air both should be treated like 1 entity, and then a 3rd guy chimes in and says, &quot;i agree&quot; and we need 24-48h on each, then the 4th guys says, &quot;sounds good&quot;.<br>
<br>
I really do agree with rig, i do not think these discussions should have been hosted here, at least without a poll, requesting permission from the majority of the RTA users.  <br>
However, due to the wishes of the majority of the guild reps involved in a '4-way conference call' - that is they wish this 'phone call' to remain private, then i believe it should be private.<br>
<br>
I'm trying to think of a time where rotations became inhibitory to guilds entering versus helpful, and I can really only think of one, which was later changed to be easier to enter.  The track record of the rotations alone, should give you some form of confidence that rotations are typically fair to all involved, and even in 'weird cases' like with doz named, that rule was placed actually to benefit all involved.<br>
<br>
Typically rotations designed for 2, are much more rough in nature, and then need a workover once others join it (there are alot less variables with 2 parties sharing, verusus several).  Seeing that the ele plane rotations are being set up for 4, I would expect them to even be 'more fair' or more refined to handle multiple parties, than most rotations that develop.<br>
<br>
I basically feel that the persons involved in the actual rotations certainly have a right to private discussions, it's silly to argue that we don't; well, because we do.  For example: if we had just set up a channel, or used tells or email instead of this board, then I doubt anyone would demand to be CC'd the emails, or demand access to the channel, or demand a transcript of my log files..  <br>
<br>
I don't think hosting them here was the best option, in fact I believe hosting them here brought about the problem. (look at this thread, hehe) -- especially without consent from RTA users. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/view.php?Emil" target="top">Emil Sinclair</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 65th Monk<br>
